  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Trim the green stalk[s] off your <strong>aubergine[s]</strong> and discard, then chop into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and dice</p><p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1700569705209-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1700569705209-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1700569705209-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1700569705209-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1700569705209-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>aubergine</strong> and <strong>diced</strong> <strong>pepper</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive</strong> <strong>oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 18-20 min or until tender – this is your <strong>roasted veg</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? You may need to do this in 2 batches!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1700569709958-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1700569709958-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1700569709958-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1700569709958-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1700569709958-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the veg is cooking, chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> roughly</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock</strong> <strong>mix</strong> and <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>paste</strong> in 175ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[230ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> – this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1700569714805-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1700569714805-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1700569714805-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1700569714805-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1700569714805-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>onion</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>coriander</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>tomatoes</strong></p><p>Cook for 2-3 min or until the tomato is beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1700569719514-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1700569719514-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1700569719514-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1700569719514-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1700569719514-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>bulgur</strong> <strong>wheat</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 7-9 min or until tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1700569725145-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1700569725145-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1700569725145-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1700569725145-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1700569725145-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the tomato has softened, add the <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>stock</strong> to the pan with 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>, the <strong>roasted</strong> <strong>veg</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong>, then bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-high and cook for 6-8 min or until thickened – this is your <strong>Georgian-style ajapsandali stew</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1700569730141-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1700569730141-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1700569730141-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1700569730141-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1700569730141-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the stew is cooking, chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Crush your <strong>walnuts</strong> in their bag with a <strong>rolling</strong> <strong>pin</strong> (keep them in the bag so you don’t lose any!)</p><p>Tip: If you don’t have a rolling pin, just chop them roughly!</p><p>Mix the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>coriander</strong> and <strong>crushed</strong> <strong>walnuts</strong> through the cooked bulgur with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> – this is your <strong>herby walnut bulgur</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1700569734497-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1700569734497-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1700569734497-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1700569734497-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1700569734497-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Georgian-style ajapsandali stew</strong> over the <strong>herby walnut bulgur</strong></p><p>Crumble your <strong>feta </strong>over the top and season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
